reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Muserise Sports Chest Bag: Your Ultimate Companion for Active Days!
reviews.reviewText: As someone who’s always on the move, finding the perfect gear to keep up with my active lifestyle is essential. The Muserise Sports Chest Bag has exceeded my expectations, and here’s why:Versatility & Style: This EDC waist bag is incredibly roomy. You can wear it as a fanny pack or sling it across your chest. It fits almost everything: portable chargers, multitools, cat treats (yes, really!), sunblock, extra pills—you name it!Quality Craftsmanship: The bag is made to last. The sturdy material ensures durability, even during rugged adventures. Plus, the zipper glides smoothly, making access a breeze.Adjustable Straps: Whether you’re a strong man or a busty girl (yes, it works for everyone!), the four adjustable straps ensure a comfortable fit. No more fumbling with ill-fitting bags!Smart Design: The multiple pockets are well-thought-out. Energy gels, your phone, and other essentials find their place effortlessly. And guess what? There’s a cool little see-through pocket on the back—perfect for a running light or other small items.Compliments Galore: People have stopped me to ask where I got this gem. Phrases like “bruh, that B is raw” and “that is a brilliant pouch” have become commonplace. It’s not just functional; it’s a style statement.Caution: Avoid wearing it with a thick screen-printed graphic tee—I learned the hard way that the combo doesn’t breathe well!In summary, the Muserise Sports Chest Bag is more than a bag; it’s a reliable companion for workouts, running, cycling, and all your outdoor adventures. Highly recommended!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Way more comfortable and useful than expected!
reviews.reviewText: This was a HUGE surprise! I bought a few products for a week long trip to Disney World. Many of the products (including this one) I was testing for the first time, and expected to be returning several of them. This rig is now going to be a permanent piece of my wardrobe and I will be buying them in different colors! It doesn't pull on my hip like a fannypack, and doesn't cause me to have a puddle down my spine in the Florida heat like a small backpack does.The Good:- Light weight but doesn't feel cheap- The zipper is great quality durable material and SMOOTH- Pocket sizes are excellent (could conceal small to mid sized tools like a toy P 30 *wink*)- The straps are comfortable and easy to adjustThe Bad:- I don't know.... The fact that I didn't notice the cool little see through pocket on the back perfect for me to put a running light in until I owned it like 3 days I guess(?)The Extra:- People complimented it with phrases like "bruh that B is raw, where'd you get it" and "that is a brilliant pouch".Caution: Don't recommend wearing with a thick screen printed graphic tee. That was the only time I became hot because the combo couldn't breath.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Overall it's pretty ok.
reviews.reviewText: I mostly kind of like this chest rig. I bought it to hold a personal protection device when I hike, ruck or run.PROS: It looks good. The zippers and fabric are great quality. Pockets are fine. Lower buckles are a cool design I haven't seen before.CONS: It would be great if tightening the straps was done by pulling the ends FORWARD instead of backward. That would make adjustments while wearing it a LOT easier. My chief complaint though is that the straps have too much stretch, which leads to bounce. I would have preferred straps that didn't stretch at all, since they are adjustable for length anyway.Almost great.
Pour le prix payé, la qualité est correcte.
Bien solide mais les attachés du haut glisse facilement si non oui je recommande

reviews.reviewText: Looks good fits good and holds your everyday essentials

reviews.reviewTitle: Good quality and fits well on chest
reviews.reviewText: This is a quality made product. It fits well on chest without slipping around or getting loose. The finish is good, the locks on the back straps are easy to unlock by pressing them without any fiddling around. One thing to remember is the straps on the back are an elastic stretch type. It fits nicely and comfortably and time will tell if these straps will start to stretch/sag or get out of shape. The front pockets are large to put a big phone in it. The zip circular grips are easy to hold to lock or unlock the zip. The back "V" shaped pocket is small and not much deep. Probably good to put something like tissues or folded papers/documents or something less valuable. I recommend this product as it suits my purpose and is comfortable.

I am amazingly surprised how well made and comfy this rig is. It's just perfect fit and didn't even have to adjust when I got it. Just right for the essentials to bring with you in trips including international. You can easily fit keys, passports etc in it so it's out of the way. No problem fumbling around as its just there on your chest. Not too intrusive or gimmicky. Basic pockets to keep your important papers and phone close to you at easy reach. Will recommend
